<p align="center" class="heading"><strong>HOW DO I BECOME an HMM CERTIFIED PHOTOGRAPHER? </strong></p>
<table width="80%"><tr><td align="left">
  <p class="cont">First, read and study all the pages in the Become an HMM Certified  Photographer section in their entirety.  The more familiar you are with  the offer and the business model, the easier it will be for you to  determine whether this opportunity is a good fit for you.</p>
  <p  class="cont">Second, complete an application.  For your convenience, you can click  below and provide your information via our secure server.  Please be  assured, we will never share your information with outside parties  unless legally required to do so.</p>
    <p  class="cont">Third, when HMM has approved your application, watch for your HMM  Certified Photographer agreement.  When received, sign and return it  with copies of your photo id and $3,500 payment.  The payment covers  your $2,500 certification fee and training materials and $1,000  promotional and marketing material startup kit.</p>
    <p  class="cont">Fourth, attend the required HMM Certified Photographer training in  Houston, TX.  Training is intensive and fast paced, so be sure you are  well-rested and can focus entirely on learning about your new business.</p>
     <p  class="cont">Fifth, begin booking business!.</p>
    
